    ns1:description """<p>Website: <a href="https://sleepanddreamdatabase.org/">sleepanddreamdatabase.org</a></p>

<p>Kelly Bulkeley, Ph.D., is a dream researcher and author with a background in the psychology of religion. He is director of the <a href="http://sleepanddreamdatabase.org/">Sleep and Dream Database (SDDb)</a>, a Senior Editor of the APA journal <a href="https://www.apa.org/pubs/journals/drm/">Dreaming</a>, and a former President of the International Association for the Study of Dreams. He earned a B.A. at Stanford University, an M.T.S. at Harvard Divinity School, and a Ph.D. from the University of Chicago Divinity School. He is currently an advisor to the <a href="https://elsewhere.to/">Elsewhere</a> dream journal app and is building the <a href="https://thedreamlibrary.net/">Dream Library Foundation</a>.</p>

